00:38:31.465 --> 00:38:33.780
to be equal to the
number of patches

00:38:33.780 --> 00:38:37.440
or transporters times the
uptake rate of each one.

00:38:37.440 --> 00:38:39.910
Because they're just not
competing against each other.

00:38:39.910 --> 00:38:42.990
And the striking thing is that
because of this difference

00:38:42.990 --> 00:38:45.670
in scaling between the
radius and the area,

00:38:45.670 --> 00:38:50.040
this can give you a
lot of uptake rate

00:38:50.040 --> 00:38:53.950
while only occupying a
small fraction of the area.

00:38:53.950 --> 00:39:01.620
This is a fraction
of area covered.

00:39:06.550 --> 00:39:09.620
Do you see why that
ends up being the case?

00:39:09.620 --> 00:39:10.552
Yes.

00:39:10.552 --> 00:39:16.150
AUDIENCE: So that's also saying
that [INAUDIBLE] pretty soon.

00:39:16.150 --> 00:39:19.830
PROFESSOR: Well, it depends
